SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 83
By Massey
A RESOLUTION to commemorate February 22, 2025, as George
Washington Day in Tennessee.
WHEREAS, George Washington, the Founding Father of the United States of America,
was born on February 22, 1732; through his unwavering dedication and exceptional leadership,
George Washington earned his place as the "Father of our Country"; and
WHEREAS, over two centuries ago, George Washington was appointed Commander-in-
Chief of the Continental Army; without pay and with steadfast resolve, he led a diverse and
untested army through eight and one-half years of war, culminating in American victory against
British forces; and
WHEREAS, his leadership at pivotal moments, including the crossing of the Delaware
River and the triumph at Yorktown, remains a testament to his courage and strategic brilliance;
and
WHEREAS, George Washington established the supremacy of civilian authority over the
military when, in 1783, he quelled a mutiny among unpaid soldiers and voluntarily resigned his
commission; he returned to private life at Mount Vernon, setting a global precedent for selfless
public service; and
WHEREAS, as president of the Constitutional Convention, George Washington provided
steady guidance as delegates drafted the U.S. Constitution, advancing the rule of law and the
ideals of liberty and justice; and
WHEREAS, unanimously elected as the first president of the United States, he
established enduring principles of governance and set an example of humility and dedication to
republican ideals by voluntarily stepping down after two terms, ensuring the peaceful transfer of
powerâ€”a cornerstone of American democracy; and
